NOW this from the very beginning.  I think of one such exMember who knew this better than anyone, acted like he supported us all the way and then left to go uber WITHOUT saying goodbye on the board, talking to any officer, particularly me, yet he still wants to &quot;hang out with us&quot; be my buddy and oh yeah, I can have one of alts, maybe, if he got off his ass to actually apply the character. BAH   I am about ready to black ball the next person who blows this kind of smoke up my a$$.  Almost every single exMember has given some lame line about how they hope there is no hard feelings <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (after they have deguilded in the middle of  night when noone is looking and some officer sees them the next day to ask WTF)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and that they will stay in touch <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (yeah right)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and maybe if they have nothing better to do, that they might think of us if they are bored.  GRRRRRRRR  I’m about ready to go evil and turn in my priest of discord book!  …But I wont because I do actually have some REAL dedicated people that would hate to see Mirwen turn evil and go rampage.  Ah the cost of lawful goodness.<br>
<br>
If you're not going to stick it out, work together to build the guild, take RESPOSIBILTY for your own part of belonging to a guild, then you do not belong in ANY decent guild, whether it is an Uber Guild, Casual guild, or RP Guild.  Plain and simple.  No matter what guild you join, you MUST put in some time and effort into being a productive member.  And oh my goodness, yes you must actually work a little.  God forbid you actually work.<br>
<br>
Yep it’s a rant forum… just had to vent. The sting of a recent stab in the back is still fresh on my mind.<br>
