<br>
You (I think) are saying an applicant is someone &quot;trialing&quot; with you and is considered an &quot;applicant&quot; for the entire Trial process during which time they are not allowed to be in a guild (for however long the trial period lasts)<br>
<br>
We on the other hand look at an Applicant as someone Inquireing about becoming a &quot;Trial&quot; and while they are &quot;trialing&quot; with us are considered (sorta junior) members of the guild with limited rights. we dont call them Applicants and they are &quot;trial&quot; members of the guild.<br>
<br>
For you, Applicant = someone in the Trial period<br>
For us Appicant = someone Inquireing about getting a trail period.<br>
<br>
I *hope* that clears things up. if I'm not right flame away, havnt gotten involved in a good one for a long time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
